<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"> <Bold>PivotGrid</Bold> :- This sample illustrates the core features of the PivotGrid control such as pivoting data through drag-and-drop operations, resizing the PivotGrid to fit content when an item group is expanded/collapsed, restricting the rowheader items from auto-resizing when more pivot items are added to the PivotComputation Area etc.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"> <Bold>PivotGrid Customization</Bold> :- This sample illustrates different ways of customizing the PivotGrid control including the visibility of subtotals present under each item group of the PivotGrid control.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"> <Bold>RowPivotsOnlyo</Bold> :- This sample illustrates multiple functionalities which can be implemented in PivotGrid by enabling the RowPivotsOnly property.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"> <Bold>UIThreading</Bold> :- This sample illustrates that the PivotGrid Control provides support to load the data in a different UI Thread. That is, the PivotGrid control can perform long running operations on a background thread so that we can access the other UI controls when the grid is loading. Tt also loads uniquely for every layout change operation, such as Filtering, Sorting, Drag and Drop, Field List, and Pivot Schema Designer.</Paragraph>
